          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "ℹ️ Color Matcher (LAB) — S-08\n\nDefaults: channels=ab, strength=1.0. mask unconnected.\n\nPRODUCTION USE CASE:\nAfter an AI pass (SDXL face refine / IPAdapter / inpaint) the output often drifts in skin tone / color cast. Feed the AI output into image_target and the pre-AI original into image_reference — S-08 re-anchors the target's chroma to the reference in LAB space.\n\nCHANNELS:\n- ab (default, pro retouch) = match chroma only, preserve target luminance. Keeps the AI output's lighting intact while pulling skin tone back toward the source.\n- lab = match L + a + b (full tone transfer). Use when the AI output has brightness drift too.\n\nSTRENGTH: 0 = identity target (bypass), 1 = full match. Typical pro dose 0.6–0.8 for natural skin-tone correction — 1.0 can look over-corrected.\n\nDEMO LIMITATION: this workflow loads sample_portrait.jpg for BOTH target and reference, so the matched output should be near-identity (proves the node runs end-to-end, not the color-shift magnitude). To see a real color transfer, replace the target LoadImage with a color-drifted version (AI output, different-temp-light copy, or a separate shoot).\n\nMASK (optional, unconnected in this demo): a binary MASK wired upstream restricts statistics computation to that region (e.g., skin-only). Output is always applied to the full target — mask only gates which pixels are used to estimate the transfer."
      ],
      "color": "#243",
      "bgcolor": "#365"
    },
